      'Is Ethereum Slipping? Bitcoin Dominance Rises AgainETH/BTC Pair: Stuck in a Downward Spiral?ETH/BTC1D ChartEthereum vs. Bitcoin. It’s the classic crypto heavyweight battle, and right now, ETH is getting pushed down the stairs. The ETH/BTC pair has been sliding since it hit that 0.041 resistance mark, right where the 0.23 Fibonacci retracement level from 2018 sits. You know those long-term Fibonacci levels—sometimes they seem like magic. They can really help spot those key areas where prices either find support to push higher or bounce lower. And right now? It’s looking like a bounce lower.Why ETH Is Struggling Against BTCSince March, ETH/BTC has been on a steady downward path. It first ran into trouble at 0.0575, another Fibonacci level (this time 0.38 from 2018), and since then, Bitcoin’s been flexing its muscles. With the launch of Bitcoin ETFs, BTC has been acting more like a stock, closely following the S&P500. Plus, Bitcoin dominance has surged, currently sitting around 58%. That’s bad news for all the altcoin pairs with BTC, including ETH.Now, here’s the thing: 0.038 is the support level to watch. If it cracks, ETH/BTC could head all the way down to 0.0316. That’s where we find the bottom of this bearish channel it’s been stuck in, and also the lower end of the reversal zone from its 2021 high when the pair made a clear top. In other words, things could get even worse for ETH if that support doesn’t hold.AI Alpha is an educational tool and does not offer financial advice.',
